This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating realistic images of human faces. It also involves machine learning techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and Siamese discriminators, which are commonly used in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of an off-the-shelf face verification system, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on training algorithms and latent spaces suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
